# Migration Safety Rules

- Never delete old paths without confirming replacement behavior.
- Migrate in phases: prepare, dual-run, switch, cleanup.
- Keep temporary adapters small and time-boxed.

## Risk Controls

- For destructive changes, add backup or revert instructions in the PR description.
- Validate critical user flows before and after each migration step.
- If unexpected repo changes appear, stop and clarify before continuing.

## Completion Criteria

- Legacy code removal happens only after production verification.
- Migration notes include what changed, why, and how to rollback.
